      "utilityType": "other",
      "description": "You conjure a two-story tower made of stone, wood, or other similar materials. The tower can be round or square in shape. Each level of the tower is 10 feet tall and has an area of up to 100 square feet. Access between levels is provided by a simple ladder and hatch. The tower has sturdy doors and windows that can be barred from the inside. You choose the furnishings and decorations of the tower, which are simple but comfortable. The tower is warm and dry, regardless of the weather outside. You can cast this spell again while it is active to maintain the tower's existence for another 24 hours. You can create a permanent tower by casting this spell in the same location and with the same configuration every day for one year.",
